root.string:
list botSearchBotOutfits(string pattern, integer matchType, integer start, integer end);
As botGetBotOutfits, except it only returns a list of bot outfits with names that match a specified pattern.  Pattern-matching is performed the same way as iwMatchString.
Passing an empty string as a pattern will act as a wildcard.  Also, using the start and end parameters, it will return a subset of the return results.

list iwSearchLinksByName(string pattern, integer matchType, integer linksOnly);
This function searches the linkset and returns a strided list of link number and link name pairs for any links with names matching the pattern, following the semantics of iwMatchString.
If the integer linksOnly is TRUE, then the function will omit the link names and only return a list of link numbers.

list iwSearchLinksByDesc(string pattern, integer matchType, integer linksOnly);
This function searches the linkset and returns a strided list of link number and link description pairs for any links with descriptions matching the pattern, following the semantics of iwMatchString.
If the integer linksOnly is TRUE, then the function will omit the link descriptions and only return a list of link numbers.
